<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="a-bit-of">a bit (of)</h1>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>有点儿；一点儿：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Could you turn the TV down a little bit?
你能把电视声音调小一点吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He felt <strong>a bit better</strong> after taking the medicine. 
吃了药，觉得好一点儿了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I wish you’d do a bit less talking and some more work.
希望你少说点话多干点活。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There’s only a bit of water left. 
只剩下一点儿水。</p></div>

<p>注: a bit常用作副词，相当于a little。修饰名词时， 需加of。  </p></div>